    <name>
      <text>Find the conditional probabilities for mutually exclusive events</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>On a firing range, a rifleman has two attempts to hit a target. The probability of hitting the target with the first shot is {@prob_first@} and the probability of hitting with the second shot is {@prob_second@}.The probability of hitting the target with both shots is {@prob_both@}. </p>
<p>Find the probability of the following events below.</p>
<p>\(M:\) "Missing the target with both shots".</p>
<p>\(P(M)=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>\(N:\) "Hitting with the first shot and missing with the second".</p>
<p>\(P(N)=\)[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Worked solution</b></p>
<p>Find the probability of the following events below.</p>
<hr>
<p>Find P(M) with \(M:\) "Missing the target with both shots".</p>
<p>To answer to this question, we denote the events \(F\), \(S\) and \(H\) as follows:</p>
<p> \(F:\) "Hitting the target with the first shot".</p>
<p> \(S:\) "Hitting the target with the second shot".</p>
<p> \(H:\) "Hitting the target with both shots".</p>
<p>We get from the information provided by the text question that \(P(F)={@prob_first@} \), \(P(S)={@prob_second@} \) and \(P(H)={@prob_both@} \).</p>
<p>Then \( P(M)=1 - P(F \cup S) \), and \( P(F \cup S)=(P(F)-P(H))+(P(S)-P(H))+P(H) \).</p>
<p>So \(P(F \cup S)=({@prob_first@} - {@prob_both@})+({@prob_second@}-{@prob_both@})+{@prob_both@}\).</p>
<p>Thus \(P(F \cup S)={@total@}\), and \( P(M)= 1-{@total@}\).</p>
<p>Therefore \(P(M)={@ta1@}\).</p>
<hr>
<p>Find P(N) with \(N:\)"hitting with the first shot and missing with the second</p>
<p> We have: \( P(N)=P(F)-P(H)\). Then</p>
<p>\( P(N)={@prob_first@}-{@prob_both@}\)</p>
<p>Therefore, \( P(N)={@ta2@}\) </p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
